                        <div class = "col-sm-6 col-sm-pull-6 main-info">
                            <p>
                                Fast forward to California! (The airplane ride was quite stale and uneventful.) Once my flight landed in Fresno, California, I hurried my way to the bus loading area and took the Yosemite Area Regional Transportation System (YARTS) from Fresno all the way to Yosemite Valley. Even though the bus ride was around two and half hours, it gave you a preview of what was in store for you when you finally arrived at your destination, which I thought was awesome. Conveniently, the bus route went right past the Yosemite Valley Lodge which was going to be my home for the next few days. I had conjured up quite the appetite during the bus route so I hastily checked in and went to my room to drop off my luggage. The place I ate at was called the Yosemite Lodge Food Court. Little did I know, this was the place where I was going to be eating the most of my meals.
